         </origination>
         <physdesc label="Quantity:"><extent>1.1 cubic feet</extent></physdesc>
         <physdesc label="Forms of Material:">Scenarios, scene blockings, company records, and correspondence.</physdesc>
         <repository label="Repository:">Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library</repository>
         <abstract label="Abstract:">Contains film scenarios and other records of the Wharton Releasing Corporation, an early motion picture company based in Ithaca, New York.</abstract>
         <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did>
      <bioghist>
         <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
         <p>The Wharton Releasing Corporation was an early motion picture movie company based in Ithaca, New York.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Scenarios, scene blockings, receipts, financial statements, a photograph of Wharton Studio, and other materials pertaining to the following silent films: "Beatrice Fairfax," "Beautiful Ireland," "The Eagle's Eye," "Knock-na-Gow" or "The Homes of Tipperary," and "Willy Reilly and His Colleen Bawn." Also, correspondence with Roman Catholic parishes and theater managers concerning leasing of films, particularly those with Irish themes, and records pertaining to the Film Company of Ireland (ca. 1921).</p>
      </scopecontent>
